cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language generation using sequence to sequence models, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of a broad coverage grammar, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the model's performance and its ability to learn syntactic rules is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of a parallel corpus and machine translation is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
